The paper deals with signal recovery from compressive sensing measurements, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The use of nonconvex penalties and optimization methods for sparse signal recovery is a common theme in machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of linear loss, which is a technique commonly used in statistical inference (cs.SI) and numerical analysis (cs.NA).
